# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Revvia site — environment variables
# Copy to `.env` for local dev. In production set these in the
# Netlify dashboard (Site settings → Environment variables).
# Anything prefixed PUBLIC_ is exposed to the browser by design.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Canonical site URL. Only override if the host/domain changes.
PUBLIC_SITE_URL="https://www.revvia.com"

# Analytics — leave blank in dev so no beacons fire locally.
# GA4 Measurement ID for the revvia.com property (NOT a client property).
PUBLIC_GA4_ID=""            # e.g. G-XXXXXXXXXX
# Meta (Facebook) Pixel ID for the agency site.
PUBLIC_META_PIXEL_ID=""     # e.g. 1234567890123456

# ── Keystatic (GitHub mode) ──────────────────────────────────
# The repo Keystatic commits to is hard-coded in keystatic.config.tsx
# (revvia-marketing/revvia-site), so no repo env var is needed.
# In production these four power the GitHub App login at /keystatic.
# In `astro dev` Keystatic uses local mode, so they're optional locally.
#
# The first three (CLIENT_ID, CLIENT_SECRET, APP_SLUG) are produced when you
# run the "Create GitHub App" flow at https://<your-site>/keystatic. The
# GitHub App's OAuth callback URL must be:
#   https://<your-site>/api/keystatic/github/oauth/callback
KEYSTATIC_GITHUB_CLIENT_ID=""              # from the GitHub App
KEYSTATIC_GITHUB_CLIENT_SECRET=""          # from the GitHub App
PUBLIC_KEYSTATIC_GITHUB_APP_SLUG=""        # the GitHub App's slug (github.com/apps/<slug>)
KEYSTATIC_SECRET=""                        # random 32-byte hex: node -e "console.log(require('crypto').randomBytes(32).toString('hex'))"

# ── Lead pipeline (configured in dashboards, NOT committed) ──
# Netlify Forms notification email is set in the Netlify UI
# (Forms → Form notifications → email Jan + Tim). No env needed.
# Google Sheet sync runs through a Make.com/Zapier scenario that
# listens to the Netlify "form submission" webhook — store that
# webhook URL in the scenario, never in the repo.
